subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Pronotum bearing an impunctate region at midline in both sexes. Anterocephalic edge in males laterally and slightly produced forward forming two subtriangular plates (
Figs. 2–4
); pronotal anterior portion devoid of concave impression and anterior edge projected forward into two subtriangular plates (
Figs 1–2
). The most remarkable feature is the morphology of male genitalia, with penis about twice as long as tegmen, very elongate, subparallel-sided, with apex hook-shaped and base spatula-shaped (
Figs 9–10
).
